is first restaurant the green frog in waycross georgia in  he later founded the red lobster inns of america and opened the first red lobster restaurant in lakeland florida in  darden chose lakeland because he wished to see how a seafood restaurant would fare in a noncoastal region and lakeland was the innermost city in florida the initial red lobster franchise was applauded by diners and critics alike the store became successful and by  had expanded to three locations in the state with two more under construction while the locations were profitable the company lacked the resources to expand further so darden sold the company to food giant general mills that year general mills ownershipedit general mills upgraded the chain to a more casual diningfamily fare oriented format opened a new company headquarters in orlando and retained darden as company manager in  when darden was promoted to vice president of general mills joseph joe r lee the companys first restaurant manager was promoted as president of red lobster under general mills ownership red lobster expanded into a chain of almost  locations by  the company underwent several restructurings and transformed itself from an inexpensive fastfood seller into a chain of casual dining seafood restaurants by  one of the companys first ventures into the diversification of its portfolio was the york steak house chain of englishthemed steak and chop restaurants in the s the franchised steak and potatoes restaurant was a cafeteriastyle restaurant with salad bar and hot station by the end of the s the chain had been mostly closed down though some independent locations still exist these places were very similar to a ruby tuesdays® now in  darden opened the first olive garden concept store in orlando the chain took off and by  general mills had opened over  stores making the chain the fastestgrowing unit in the companys restaurant holdings while olive garden did not meet critical success it was popular and its perstore sales soon grew to match those of red lobster the company eventually became the largest chain of italianthemed fullservice restaurants in the united states in  china coast was launched as an attempt to create a us national casual dining restaurant that featured american chinese cuisine while the chain eventually expanded to some  restaurants its sales were lackluster and lost an estimated  million usd by the end of  the company was shuttered and the remaining locations were either converted to red lobsters or olive gardens or closed altogether dardenedit in  general mills decided to spin off its restaurant chains to focus on consumer food products the new company was named darden restaurants after red lobsters founder general mills stockholders received one share of darden for every common share of general mills held general mills restaurants had  million net income in that year at the end of  darden operated  restaurants in  states with  locations in canada darden restaurants was spun off from general mills beginning on may   when it began trading on whenissue basis at  a share the company became a fully separate entity on may   when its shares went on sale on the nyse the shares opened at   below expectations but climbed to  by the close of trading darden executives planned to have two additional chains in place by  in march  darden launched a test of bahama breeze caribbean grille concept featuring food and drinks found in the islands of the caribbean sea and a caribbean theme was created in  markets were over saturated with restaurants in  forcing darden to close  poor performing locations and lose  million due to the restructuring red lobster and olive garden were given make overs in  darden also made a profit of  million that year  saw darden opening additional location after recovering from the  losses the company then began testing a new concept entitled smokey bones bbq sports bar that opened in late  in orlando the restaurant is a sports bar concept featuring barbecue and related foodstuffs in an appalachian mountainlodge setting in  seasons  was under development with the idea of provide guests the opportunity to indulge while still eating well season  were only being opened in the florida or atlanta markets during its initial phase darden announced in january  that the company was willing to expand by purchasing an existing  location chains even considering franchisors by may darden indicated that its smokey bones division would be sold and or shut down including the two rocky river grillhouse the proposed replacement concept for smokey bones in august darden acquired rival atlantabased restaurant holder rare hospitality for  billion usd gaining rares two chains the capital grille and longhorn steakhouse as part of the rare acquisition darden set up its specialty restaurant group to include capital grille bahama breeze and seasons  in december darden announced that it would sell its smokey bones chain to barbeque integrated inc an affiliate of sun capital partners inc for approximately  million the sale was completed in january  expansion and ownership changesedit in  seasons  started a new expansion phase opening up in  more states over the next three years in january  darden announced colocating their olive garden and red lobster brands in smaller markets to share kitchen but continue separate menus and eating areas as part of the february darden analyst conference an analyst indicated that the corporation may be targeting another restaurant chain for acquisition possibly one of bjs california pizza kitchen or yard house in october  darden acquired  chains eddie v’s prime seafood and wildfish seafood grille for  million cash transaction and were placed within its specialty restaurant group also in october darden signed an areadevelopment agreement with americana group of kuwait to develop and operate at least  locations using the red lobster olive garden and longhorn steakhouse concepts in july  darden acquired the yard house  location beercentric chain for  million from tsg consumer partners yard house will be alongside the other upscale restaurants in dardens specialty restaurant group on december   dardens stock rose  percent after activist investor starboard value a hedge fund took a stake in the company red lobster saleedit on december   darden announced plans to sell or spinoff the red lobster brand citing pressure from stock investors this was in direct response to the company spending us million on a new digital platform at the time the project was already at least one year behind schedule and above budget a large number of layoffs occurred in its marketing department and the companys second in command also left on may   darden announced that as part of the spinoff of red lobster it was converting the colocated red lobster and olive garden locations into standalone olive garden locations on may   darden announced it would be selling the red lobster seafood restaurant chain to golden gate capital for us billion darden announced the completion of the sale of red lobster on july   acquisitionsedit differences between starboard and darden management soon emerged over the hedge funds proposal to split the company in two and spin off a third to handle their real estate portfolio a move starboard said would greatly boost shareholder value matters came to head when management announced a plan to spin off the underperforming red lobster early in  starboard led a large group of investors in asking management to delay the move and see if better options such as its plans to revitalize the chain were available when management instead decided to sell the chain to private equity firm golden gate capital in may starboard and other investors sharply criticized the  billion fire sale price as a serious undervaluing of red lobster and its assets such as the underlying real estate it also claimed management had refused shareholders requests for a special meeting to discuss the deal chief executive officer clarence otis jr announced he would be resigning at the end of the year the same day the red lobster sale was complete management said afterwards that it would work on a needed turnaround plan for olive garden also struggling however after cnbc reported on a leaked document supposedly offered to potential lenders and buyers earlier in the year that described red lobsters financial position far more optimistically than management had in its contemporary public statements one of the investors a union pension fund filed suit alleging material misrepresentation management claimed the document had been prepared by golden gate in consultation with red lobsters executives who could have been expected to have that view of the chains future eugene lee was named permanent ceo on february   after serving as interim ceo in october  starboard assembled its own slate of directors to challenge all the sitting board members in the companys upcoming shareholder elections in support of their candidacy it released a slide presentation in early september about how the company had gone wrong and how its directors would restore it to health while it received considerable media attention for its detailed focus on olive garden in particular the chains wasteful practice of serving too many of its free unlimited breadsticks at once to prevent food waste due to staleness instead of one per customer plus an additional one per table additional breadsticks are served fresh on demand and not salting the water it boiled pasta in so as to secure a longer warranty on the pots it also attacked management for spending lavishly on the chains corporate headquarters while paying the general managers of individual restaurants less than its competitors did management responded two days later that it was already implementing many of the suggested changes and said the free breadsticks merely represented italian generosity nevertheless in october shareholders replaced the entire board with starboards slate in what an observer called an epic fail for management since that rarely happens on march   darden announced its intent to acquire cheddars scratch kitchen for  million from shareholders such as l catterton and oak investment partners on march   when darden announced it that had acquired cheddars scratch kitchen and lifted its fullyear earnings outlook the company became the biggest gainer that day on the sp  with shares growing nearly  percent the acquisition was completed on april   unitsedit longhorn steakhouse olive garden cheddars scratch kitchen darden’s specialty restaurant group eddie vs prime seafood the capital grille bahama breeze seasons  fresh grill and wine bar with a seasonal menu with containing  or fewer calories  yard house usa inc   locationscitation needed darden corporation gmri inc rare hospitality international inc rare hospitality management inc see alsoedit food portal list of restaurant chains list of food companies list of casual dining restaurant chains list of sp  companies companies listed on the new york stock exchange d list of florida companies list of orlando companies list of michigan companies referencesedit  a b c d e darden restaurants company profile hoovers inc  answerscom june   accessed on june    a b c darden restaurants form k annual report filing date jul   pdf secdatabasecom retrieved mar     a b darden  annual report pdf darden restaurants inc retrieved april     darden restaurants inc may   fy  k us securities and exchange commission retrieved april     pedicini sandra olive garden tries to woo back customers after falling into a rut mcclatchytribune newspapers at chicago tribune january   retrieved on january    a b marketwatchcom darden restaurants inc the new york times retrieved  permanent dead link  a b c d e f g h darden restaurants international directory of company histories the gale group inc  answerscom  jun  accessed november    sam reading  york steak house photo galley smugmugcom retrieved    tra